cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.FL

This paper proposes a redesign of Prolog with alternative semantics, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses reasoning about programs and tools such as a partial evaluator, which relates to logic in computer science (cs.LO) and software engineering (cs.SE). The use of disjunction, conjunction, and unification as primitive goal types relates to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses control constructs and module composition mechanisms, which relate to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
